parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt mechanism can prevent the seat belt from functioning properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt tongue seizes in place
the seat belt release button breaks
the seat belt buckle fails to latch
the seat belt clip pops back out of the buckle
the seat belt mechanism fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure due to Bubbles in the Tread/Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of all four tires can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: bubbles or blisters on the tire tread or sidewall

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause antifreeze to leak, leading to engine overheating, damage to the engine and surrounding components, and potentially resulting in a breakdown or accident.
symptoms: white smoke or steam comes from the exhaust pipe.
